de.dezibel.data

Class Genre

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.dezibel.data.Genre

  • public class Genre
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a genre which can be used to classify the Medium objects. A genre can have a maximum of one super genre but any amount of sub-genres.
    Author:
    Henner

    • Method Detail

      • delete

        public void delete()
        Completely removes this genre from the database and all associated genres. Will do nothing if this genre is the default top-genre.
        Precondition:
        This genre is not the default top-genre.
        Postcondition:
        This genre is deleted from the database, its super-genre's sub-genres and its sub-genres' super-genre.

      • addMedium

        public void addMedium(Medium medium)
        Adds medium to the media of this genre. If medium already was associated with this genre, nothing will happen.
        Parameters:
        medium - The medium you wish to add to this genre.
        Precondition:
        medium must is not null.
        Postcondition:
        self.hasMedium(medium)

        Precondition:

      • removeMedium

        public void removeMedium(Medium medium)
        Removes medium from the media of this genre. If medium wasn't associated with this genre in the first place, nothing will happen.
        Parameters:
        medium - The medium to be removed from this genre's media.
        Precondition:
        medium is not null
        Postcondition:

      • removeSubGenre

        public void removeSubGenre(Genre subGenre)

        Parameters:
        subGenre - The genre to be removed from this genre's sub-genres.
        Precondition:

        Postcondition:

      • setSuperGenre

        public void setSuperGenre(Genre superGenre)
        Sets this genre's super-genre to superGenre. Will do nothing if this genre equals the default top-genre. If superGenre equals null the default top-genre from the database is chosen instead.
        Parameters:
        superGenre - This genre's new super genre.
        Precondition:
        This genre must not be the default top-genre.
        Postcondition:
        This genre's super-genre is now superGenre or the default top-genre.
